questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;to make excuses or do things to gain time&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;An idiom is&amp;nbsp;a&amp;nbsp;group&amp;nbsp;of words in a&amp;nbsp;fixed&amp;nbsp;order&amp;nbsp;that has a&amp;nbsp;particular&amp;nbsp;meaning&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;that is different from the&amp;nbsp;meanings&amp;nbsp;of each word on&amp;nbsp;its&amp;nbsp;own.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For example&lt;/strong&gt;: Rain cats and dogs: to rain very heavily.

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;The sky suddenly turned gray and it rained cats and dogs for almost an hour.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;given idiom &amp;quot;play for time&amp;quot; means to make excuses and delay until you are ready&lt;/strong&gt;.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: My&amp;nbsp;computer&amp;nbsp;crashed&amp;nbsp;just&amp;nbsp;as&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;meeting&amp;nbsp;began,&amp;nbsp;so&amp;nbsp;I&amp;nbsp;had&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;play&amp;nbsp;for&amp;nbsp;time&amp;nbsp;while&amp;nbsp;I&amp;nbsp;waited&amp;nbsp;for&amp;nbsp;it&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;reboot.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the given explanation it is clear that the meaning of the given idiom is &amp;quot;To make excuses or do things to gain time&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the &lt;strong&gt;correct answer is option 2)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Let us have a look at&amp;nbsp; some commonly used idioms:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:500px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Idiom&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meaning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;It is a piece of cake&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;It is easy&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Let the cat out of the bag&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;To reveal a secret&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Break a leg&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Good luck&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Hit the sack&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Go to sleep&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;taken unawares, without the chance to dispose of&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: 700; display: inline !important;&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in the incorrect usage of the &lt;strong&gt;phrasal verb.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dispose of&lt;/strong&gt;: It is a phrasal verb which means&amp;nbsp;to get rid of someone or something or deal with something so that the matter is finished.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;It took only five minutes for the world champion to dispose of (= defeat) his opponent.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the correct sentence is:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;The suspect was taken unawares, without the chance to dispose of the evidence.&amp;#39;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Phrasal verb:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;a phrase that consists of a verb with a preposition or adverb or both, the meaning of which is different from the meaning of its separate parts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Unbeatable&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;invincible&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means too powerful to be defeated or overcome. (अजेय)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;His invincible spirit helped him survive against all odds.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Unbeatable&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to someone or something that cannot be defeated or surpassed. (अपराजेय)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The team&amp;rsquo;s unbeatable record speaks volumes about their dedication and hard work.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, we can infer that the word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;invincible&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; can be replaced by &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;unbeatable&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; without changing the meaning of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Unbeatable&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unmanageable&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;अप्रबंधनीय&lt;/span&gt;): Difficult or impossible to manage or control.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The unmanageable workload caused a lot of stress among employees.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inviolable&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;अभंग&lt;/span&gt;): Never to be broken, infringed, or dishonored.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The right to freedom of speech is an inviolable principle in a democracy.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Immeasurable&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;असीम&lt;/span&gt;): Too large, extensive, or extreme to measure.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The benefits of good health are immeasurable.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Question: He could rise to the stature because of his invincible courage.&lt;/p&gt;

