questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;i-B, ii-A, iii-D, iv-C&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let us see the meanings of the words in the given options:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Concord&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means &lt;strong&gt;accord &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;or harmony between people or groups&lt;/strong&gt;. It matches the meaning of &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Agreement&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Condign&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is used while referring to&lt;strong&gt; some punishment&lt;/strong&gt;; it means&lt;strong&gt; &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;appropriate to the crime or &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;wrongdoing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;; fitting and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;deserved&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;. It matches the meaning of &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fitting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Penitent&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means &lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;feeling or showing &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;sorrow&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt; and regret for having done wrong&lt;/strong&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;It matches the meaning of &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contrite&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Labile&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;liable to change; easily altered&lt;/strong&gt;. It matches the meaning of &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Volatile&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the above reference, we can see that the correct combination of matching is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;i-B, ii-A, iii-D, iv-C&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;, which is given in &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;B&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in the &lt;strong&gt;second part&lt;/strong&gt; of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;more&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is grammatically incorrect in the third part of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;more&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; (&lt;strong&gt;comparative degree&lt;/strong&gt;) should be replaced with &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;most&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; (&lt;strong&gt;superlative degree&lt;/strong&gt;) to make the sentence correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in &lt;strong&gt;superlative form &lt;/strong&gt;(as we are not comparing only two things), thus &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;most&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct option is B.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct sentence is:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;He was one of the &lt;strong&gt;most &lt;/strong&gt;unfortunate people&amp;nbsp;in the world.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;  &quot;&gt;&amp;#39;More&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the comparative form of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;  &quot;&gt;much&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;  &quot;&gt;many&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;. It indicates a greater amount or number than that is indicated by much or many.&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;I need more time to finish the work.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;  &quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Most&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the superlative form of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;  &quot;&gt;many&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;  &quot;&gt;much&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;. It indicates the greatest in number, quantity, etc. In comparisons,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;  &quot;&gt;most&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;normally used with&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;  &quot;&gt;the.&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;  &quot;&gt;​Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Those who have&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the most&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;money are not always the happiest.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/21/01/hin1.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 200px; height: 92px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;वाक्य के तीसरे भाग में &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;more&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; व्याकरणिक रूप से गलत है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;वाक्य को सही बनाने के लिए &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;more&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; (comparative form) को &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;most&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; (superlative form) से प्रतिस्थापित किया जाना चाहिए।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;दिया गया वाक्य &lt;strong&gt;superlative form&lt;/strong&gt; में है (क्योंकि हम केवल दो चीजों की तुलना नहीं कर रहे हैं), इस प्रकार &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;most&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; का प्रयोग किया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;more&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;much&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;और &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;many&lt;/span&gt; का comparative form&amp;nbsp;है। यह अधिक राशि या संख्या को इंगित करता है जो much या many द्वारा इंगित की जाती है।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;I need more time to finish the work.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
