&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The incorrect spelling among above mentioned options is &amp;#39;conconitant&amp;#39;. Its correct spelling is &lt;strong&gt;concomitant&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;#39;s find out the meanings of following words :-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bourgeois :- A self-confessed and proud person.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Perceptible - A&amp;nbsp;slight movement or change of state that is&amp;nbsp;able to be seen or noticed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anachronistic -&amp;nbsp;belonging to a period other than that being portrayed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Concomitant - Phenomenon&amp;nbsp;that&amp;nbsp;naturally accompanies or follows something.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, option 4 i.e. &amp;#39;conconitant&amp;#39; is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;option 1)&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/09/428%20%281%29.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 48px; height: 48px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Explanation:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;​&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;We need to follow these instructions while changing the voice of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;an assertive sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Identify the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;subject and object&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given sentence and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;interchange&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;their places.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;Another museum&amp;#39; becomes the subject in the passive voice and &amp;#39;The Archaeological Survey of India&amp;#39; becomes the object in passive voice.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use the preposition &amp;lsquo;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;by&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;before the agent.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;is/ are + ing&amp;#39; form of verb in active voice changes to &amp;#39;is/are + being + V&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;&amp;#39; in passive voice.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Lastly, line up the remaining part.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lastly, line up the remaining part.-&amp;quot;&lt;em&gt;Another museum is being built by the Archaeological Survey of India to house excavated objects from across the country.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

The correct answer is-&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;​Experienced difficulty&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate meaning of the given idiom&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hit a bad patch&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Experienced difficulty​&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s look at the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;meaning and example&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given phrasal verb:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hit a bad patch&lt;/span&gt;- &amp;quot;To experience or be in the midst of a period of trouble, difficulty, or hardship.&amp;quot; (परेशानी, कठिनाई या कठिनाई के दौर का अनुभव करना या होना।)
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;E.g.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Our marriage &lt;strong&gt;hit a bad patch&lt;/strong&gt; after Frank lost his job, but now our relationship is stronger than ever.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;​​&lt;/em&gt;Thus from the explanation given above, we find that the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;3rd&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;option&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct choice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; 4) Sedulous&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word&lt;strong&gt; &amp;quot;conscientious&amp;quot; (ईमानदार)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;means&lt;strong&gt; to be diligent, thorough, and attentive in performing tasks or duties. &lt;/strong&gt;A conscientious person is careful, responsible, and takes their work seriously.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example: &amp;quot;Mary is a &lt;strong&gt;conscientious &lt;/strong&gt;student who always submits her assignments on time and puts in extra effort to ensure the quality of her work.&amp;quot;

		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;In this example, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;conscientious&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; describes Mary&amp;#39;s diligent and responsible approach to her academic tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Sedulous&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(परिश्रमी)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;means&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt; diligent, assiduous, and hardworking,&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt; sharing similar traits with being conscientious.&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;Despite facing numerous challenges, Sarah remained &lt;strong&gt;sedulous &lt;/strong&gt;in her pursuit of academic excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In summary, the word that is closest in meaning (synonym) to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;conscientious&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;4) Sedulous.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Now let&amp;#39;s examine the other options:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Savage (असभ्य):&lt;/strong&gt; This option is not a synonym for &amp;quot;conscientious.&amp;quot; &amp;quot;Savage&amp;quot; means brutal, fierce, or cruel, which has a completely different meaning.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Casual (अनौपचारिक):&lt;/strong&gt; This option is the opposite of &amp;quot;conscientious.&amp;quot; While &amp;quot;conscientious&amp;quot; implies careful and diligent behavior, &amp;quot;casual&amp;quot; denotes a relaxed or informal approach, often associated with not paying close attention to details or responsibilities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Carefree (लापरवाह):&lt;/strong&gt; This option does not have the same meaning as &amp;quot;conscientious.&amp;quot; &amp;quot;Carefree&amp;quot; refers to being lighthearted, without worries or concerns, and does not convey the sense of diligence and responsibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is- &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Depraved&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the marked option:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Depraved:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;morally bad or evil (नैतिक रूप से बुरा या बुरा)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Someone who can kill a child like that must be totally&lt;strong&gt; depraved&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the other given options:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deprecate​:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to not approve of something or say that you do not approve of something (किसी बात का अनुमोदन न करना या यह कहना कि आप किसी चीज़ को स्वीकार नहीं करते हैं)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detrimental​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;causing harm or damage (नुकसान या क्षति पहुंचाना)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diatribe​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;an angry speech or piece of writing that severely criticizes something or someone (एक क्रोधित भाषण या लेखन का टुकड़ा जो किसी चीज या किसी की गंभीर आलोचना करता है)&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, from the given meanings, we find that&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Depraved&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct one-word substitute.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Contemptous&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct spelling for &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Contemptous&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;should be &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Contemptuous&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Contemptuous&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;means showing contempt; scornful.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The incorrect spelling &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Contemptous&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is missing the letter &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;u&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;after &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;p&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;All other options are correctly spelled and are commonly used words with clear definitions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Correcting the spelling to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Contemptuous&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;aligns with standard English spelling conventions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Option 3&amp;quot;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Credulous: &lt;/strong&gt;This means having too great a readiness to believe things; gullible.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contagious: &lt;/strong&gt;This refers to (of a disease) spread from one person or organism to another by direct or indirect contact.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consensus: &lt;/strong&gt;This means a general agreement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;She asked her husband why he had left the door open.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Direct Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;As per the given question we have to change it into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Indirect Speech.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process of transformation as follows:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;There will be no change in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;reporting&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;verb&lt;/span&gt;. Because&amp;nbsp;we know that the given sentence is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;interrogative&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;with a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;question&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;word&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Comma and inverted commas&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be removed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Why&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be used as a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;conjunction&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;because we know that in an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;interrogative&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;sentence with a question word the question word itself becomes the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;conjunction&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;You&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be changed into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;he&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;because in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;direct to indirect transformation&amp;#39; second-person pronoun (you)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is changed according to the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;object&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of reporting verb that is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;her husband&amp;#39;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Did leave&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be changed into &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;had left&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;(Direct to Indirect)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;She asked her husband why he had left the door open.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Change in adverbs&amp;nbsp;and determines in Direct To Indirect Speech.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
