&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;To be alert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The idiom &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;On the ball&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; means to become&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;very alert and aware of what is happening. (क्या हो रहा है इसके बारे में बहुत सतर्क और जागरूक होना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;For example-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The mother is glad to know that her son is always &lt;u&gt;on the ball &lt;/u&gt;to learn new things in class.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;So, it is clear that the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;appropriate meaning of the idiom &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;On the ball&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;to be alert&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some compound expressions or phrases act as conjunctions. Expressions such as even if, so that, as well as, as if, in order that are called Compound Conjunctions. In this case, &amp;#39;on condition that&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp; is the correct compound conjunction.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I agreed to come to the party on condition that he will not be there.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will excuse you this time &lt;strong&gt;on the condition that &lt;/strong&gt;you do not repeat the blunder.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Backbones&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;In the opening sentence &amp;#39;Life processes are similar in all animals with (1)______. &amp;#39; we can see that our subject is a &lt;strong&gt;plural subject&lt;/strong&gt; and so the given blank is also a plural subject as per the grammatical rule of parallelism.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;From the given options ,&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;backbones&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is the most appropriate option to be filled in the given blank as it is a &lt;strong&gt;plural noun.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;such as&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The given sentence &amp;#39; So physiologists can find out a lot about the human body by studying animals (2)______ frogs, rats and ,rabbits.&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;conveys that physiologists study animals &lt;b&gt;including&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;frogs, rats,&amp;nbsp; and rabbits to find out a lot about our human body.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The given blank is &lt;strong&gt;filled&lt;/strong&gt; with a word that is similar to the&lt;strong&gt; above-given&lt;/strong&gt; context.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;From the given options , &lt;strong&gt;Such as&lt;/strong&gt; is used to provide examples of the same type.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Including is the synonym of &amp;#39;such as&amp;#39; and in the above sentence &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Such as&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is the most appropriate word as it gives examples of animals of the same type.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Therefore, the correct answer is o&lt;strong&gt;ption 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;hurt&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;From the given options, we need to choose the appropriate word that will fill the &lt;strong&gt;blank number 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The given sentence &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;But, physiologists take great care to not (3)______ the animals&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;#39; conveys that Physiologists look after not to harm the animals.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The marked option &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;hurt&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; means&amp;nbsp;to cause physical pain or injury, to harm or damage in some way.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Therefore, the most appropriate word is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;hurt&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; as per the given meaning above and it fits well in the &lt;strong&gt;blank number 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Thus, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;usually&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence &amp;#39;The animals are (4)______ put to sleep during the experiments.&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp; we need to fill the &lt;strong&gt;blank number 4 with the correct adverb&lt;/strong&gt; from the given options.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We can choose the correct option after exploring the usage of each adverb given in the options.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Oddly&lt;/strong&gt; is used to show that something is Surprising and it means in an unusual and interesting way; unexpectedly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strangely &lt;/strong&gt;is similar in usage to Oddly as it means in an unusual way.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Usually&lt;/strong&gt; is used to talk about what happens on most occasions or in most situations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Incidentally&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is used for adding related information; in a way that is not planned.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;After going through each and every option, we can say that &amp;#39;Usually&amp;#39; is the most appropriate word to be filled in the &lt;strong&gt;blank number 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;that&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;In the given sentence &amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;It is only by physiological research (5)______ medicine has been able to advance &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; requires an appropriate word from the given options to be filled in the blank number 5.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp; Marked option&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;that&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is used for introducing a clause stating a fact.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;In the above sentence &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;that&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be used in the given blank as it states the fact why medicine has been able to advance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Rearrange the parts of the sentence in correct order.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The information gleaned&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;P. both the movement and the musculature of&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Q. living animal species help scientists model&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;R. how non-avian dinosaurs may have moved&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S. from fossil bones along with observations of&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SPQR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While arranging the parts of the sentence, we have to understand the overall meaning, determine the sentence type ,and find some grammatical or contextual relationships between the parts. So let&amp;#39;s find them out.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part S&lt;/strong&gt; comes first as it continues the sentence and the meaning started: &lt;em&gt;The information gleaned&lt;strong&gt; from fossil bones along with observations of...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; So, it will be put in the &lt;strong&gt;first place&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part P&lt;/strong&gt; follows &lt;strong&gt;Part S &lt;/strong&gt;and describes the extra information that is gathered besides the fossil bones (&lt;em&gt;The information gleaned&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;from fossil bones along with observations of &lt;strong&gt;both the movement and the musculature of...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;). So, it will be put in the &lt;strong&gt;second place&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part Q&lt;/strong&gt; follows &lt;strong&gt;Part P. &lt;/strong&gt;It specifies whose movement and musculature are in discussion: &lt;em&gt;The information gleaned&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;from fossil bones along with observations of both the movement and the musculature of &lt;strong&gt;living animal species help scientists model...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; So, it will be put in the &lt;strong&gt;third place&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part R&lt;/strong&gt; comes at the end. It is the continuation of previous parts as it gives the object of the whole sentence and tells us what the scientists are trying to model.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, as per the points mentioned above, we find that the correct order is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;SPQR&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the sentence in the correct order is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The information gleaned from fossil bones along with observations of both the movement and the musculature of living animal species help scientists model how non-avian dinosaurs may have moved.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parts of a sentence are given below in jumbled order. Select the option that arranges the parts in the correct order to form a meaningful sentence.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A. with a supreme sense of rhythm and word appeal;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;B. he was capable of writing angelic or weird poetry,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C. or the outlines of an unrelenting plot in a hard and dry style&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;D. yet he would write down a problem of morbid psychology&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;B, A, D, C.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B&lt;/strong&gt;: This part introduces the subject (he) and sets the tone for the sentence by describing the subject&amp;#39;s capability in writing.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt;: This part provides additional information about the subject&amp;#39;s writing style, specifying that he writes with a supreme sense of rhythm and word appeal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D&lt;/strong&gt;: This part introduces a contrast or contradiction in the subject&amp;#39;s writing style, mentioning that despite his capability to write angelic or weird poetry, he also writes about a problem of morbid psychology.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt;: This part concludes the sentence by further expanding on the subject&amp;#39;s diverse writing style, stating that he can also write about the outlines of an unrelenting plot in a hard and dry style.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So, the sequence flows logically from introducing the subject&amp;#39;s capability, providing additional details about his writing style, introducing a contrast, and then concluding with another aspect of his writing style.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
